run npm init
add .gitignore to ignore node_modules file,
run npm install --save express, 
run npm install --save-dev nodemon(so you dont have to run development server again and aagin)
Go to package.json and add a "start" script in the scripts session and execute nodemon app.js to start app.js with nodemon. as in "start": "nodemon app.js"
Go to app.js and setup node js server.
run npm install --save body-parser(to be able to parse incoming request).

Create your routed folder and add your routes.

create your controllers folder.


res.render() wont be called anymore because rest api only deals with data.


note: there should be different domains for frontend and backend, so therefore we need the CORS headers.

